Police in Houston say a 34-year-old man got behind the wheel of his car while under the influence Sunday , killing two people , one of them a 6-year boy boy .
Blaine Boudreaux has been charged with intoxication manslaughter , intoxicated assault and failure to stop and render aid involving death in connection to at least three DUI collisions that took place within three hours in Houston .
The 34-and-old , was allegedly drunk when he ran a red light on Lockwood Drive and led to the death of a homeless man .